1025 is the SMTP port of mailhog server
8025 is the HTTP port of mailhog server

A mailable class defines how an email message should be built.

php artisan make:mail MyMail
// config for laravel to know we are using mailhog server
MAIL_HOST=127.0.0.1
php artisan make:controller EmailController
php artisan make:view my_mail

php artisan config:cache
php artisan config:clear        // to clear the config cache, will fix errors


default middleware are registered in app/Http/Kernel.php
in the web.php

in_array(value, [e1, e2]) function is used to check whether a value exists in an array or not.
    returns true or false



